## Output Format

When you have completed ALL work, output ONLY valid JSON in one of these formats:

**If work is completed successfully:**
```json
{
  "type": "completed",
  "summary": "description of what was accomplished",
  "metadata": {
    "files_modified": ["path/to/file.rs"],
    "files_created": [],
    "files_deleted": [],
    "tests_run": true,
    "tests_passed": true,
    "build_checked": true,
    "build_passed": true
  }
}
```

**If work cannot be completed:**
```json
{
  "type": "failed",
  "reason": "explanation of why the work cannot be completed"
}
```

**If work is blocked waiting for clarification:**
```json
{
  "type": "blocked",
  "reason": "what information or access you need to proceed"
}
```

The `metadata` field is optional but helps track what was done.
